<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870505-0079 </DOCNO><HL> L.E. Myers Co. HoldingRaised by Chicago Investor</HL><DD> 05/05/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MYRTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Leonard Chavin, a Chicago investor who has said he may seek control of L.E. Myers Co. Group, disclosed that he raised his stake in the company to 14.6% of the common shares outstanding from 13.2%.    In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Mr. Chavin said he controls 329,300 Myers common shares, including 30,500 purchased April 21 through last Thursday at $5.874 to $6.125 each.    L.E. Myers performs construction services for electric utilities.    As reported previously, Mr. Chavin has asked for a seat on the Myers board and still is considering alternatives for seeking control of the company.    In Oak Brook, Ill., Elliott Robbins, senior vice president and chief financial officer of L.E. Myers, confirmed that the company is considering Mr. Chavin for board membership. Mr. Robbins had no comment on Mr. Chavin's increased stake.    Mr. Chavin couldn't be reached for comment. </TEXT></DOC>